{
  "doc_id": "58931",
  "text": "Various 400 mm × 400 mm panels of FMLs were manufactured and tested under localised blast at the University of Cape Town from 0.025 in thick sheets of 2024-0 aluminium alloy and a woven glassglass fibre/propylene composite. The FML panels tested had exposed areas of 300 mm × 300 mm unanimously and were labelled AXTYZ-#, where A = aluminium, X = number of aluminium layers, T = GFPP, Y = number of blocks of GFPP, Z = number of plies of GFPP per block and # indicates the panel number [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
